comments:
The part in Warwickshire was part of the parish of Great 
    Wolford until 25.3.1885; on 30.9.1896 this became part of Gloucestershire, so that thereafter Batsford was wholly in 
    Gloucestershire. See also Table 2, note (b).

Transferred from Worcestershire to Gloucestershire on 1.4.1931. 
    See also Table 2, note (b).

In 1894 the part in Gloucestershire  became 
    part of the parish of Admington, so that thereafter Ilmington was wholly in 
    Warwickshire. See also Table 2, note (e).

Transferred from Worcestershire to Warwickshire on 1.4.1931. See 
    also Table 2, note (e).

Transferred from Gloucestershire to Warwickshire on 20.10.1844. 
    See also Table 2, note (e).

Transferred from Worcestershire to Warwickshire on 1.4.1931. See 
    also Table 2, note (e).

Transferred from Worcestershire to Warwickshire on 1.4.1931. See 
    also Table 2, note (e).
